      {{#freestyle-note "edit-form-child-components--notes"}}
        The edit-form component yields 2 child components `controls` and `inputs`. It also has 5 properties `isEditing`, `isSaving`, `isCanceling`, `isRunning`, and `isDisabled`.

        `{{isEditing}}`
        This is a boolean that is true if the form is in an editing state.

        `{{isSaving}}`
        This is a boolean that is true if the form is running the save action.

        `{{isCanceling}}`
        This is a boolean that is true if the form is running the cancel action.

        `{{isRunning}}`
        This is a boolean that is true if the form is running either the save or the cancel action.

        `{{isDisabled}}`
        This is a boolean that is true if the form inputs should be in a disabled state because the form is editing or running an action.

        `{{controls}}`
        This subcomponent represents the controls for the form. It has 3 child components `cancelButton`, `saveButton`, and `editButton`. It also has 4 properties `isEditing`, `isSaving`, `isCanceling`, and `isRunning`.

        `{{controls.isEditing}}`
        This is a boolean that is true if the form is in an editing state.

        `{{controls.isSaving}}`
        This is a boolean that is true if the form is running the save action.

        `{{controls.isCanceling}}`
        This is a boolean that is true if the form is running the cancel action.

        `{{controls.isRunning}}`
        This is a boolean that is true if the form is running either the save or the cancel action.

        `{{controls.cancelButton}}`
        This is the cancel button for the form

        `{{controls.editButton}}`
        This is the edit button for the form.

        `{{controls.saveButton}}`
        This is the save button for the form.


        `{{inputs}}`
        This is a component that contains the inputs for the form.
      {{/freestyle-note}}
